<h1 align="center"><font size="7" color="#FF00FF"><b>&quot;Language&quot;</b></font></h1>
<div align="center"><center>

<table border="0" width="80%" cellpadding="0" height="386">
  <tr>
    <td align="left" height="38"><h4 align="left"><font size="6" color="#0000FF"><u>Language</u></font></h4>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td align="left" height="88"><ul>
      <li><font size="6" color="#0000FF">you follow a set of rules and syntax to markup your
        document.</font></li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Rule #1: Remember the XML declaration</h2>
    <p class="code">&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; standalone=&quot;yes/no&quot;
    encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;</p>
    <h2>Rule #2: Do what the DTD instructs</h2>
    <p class="copy">&nbsp;The XML document will validate against the specified DTD.</p>
    <h2>Rule #3: Watch your capitalization</h2>
    <p class="copy">&lt;YANWANG&gt; is not&nbsp; &lt;YanWang&gt;.</p>
    <h2>Rule #4: Quote attribute values</h2>
    <p class="code">&lt;NAME dateofbirth=&quot;1974&quot;&gt;Nan Chen&lt;/NAME&gt;</p>
    <h2>Rule #5: Close all tags</h2>
    <p class="copy">&lt;P&gt;...&lt;/P&gt;</p>
    <h2>Rule #6: Close Empty tags, too</h2>
    <p class="copy">&lt;br/&gt; </td>
  </tr>
